               <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bibl821-1">Rahmani, Studia syriaca, I, 35-36; BHO, 501- 502. R. Beulay, dans PdO 8 {1977- 78) , 90- 95. BSO, I, 1113 (J. Habbi).</quote>
               </note>
               <note type="abstract">John Bar Penkaye was a monk of the convent of John of Kamul, southwest of Mount Gudi.  He spent time with superior Sawrisho, whom he had healed from leprosy.  His text Ris Mele treats the Muslim conquest.  </note>
